DSA (Data Structures & Algorithms) in Python programming covers the same core concepts as any other language, but implemented using Python’s syntax and built in features. Below is a complete, structured list of DSA topics, from basics to advanced, with Python context.
________________________________________
1. Python Basics for DSA (Prerequisites)
Before DSA, you should be comfortable with:
•	Variables and data types
•	if, for, while loops
•	Functions
•	Recursion
•	Time & space complexity basics (Big O notation)
________________________________________
2. Core Data Structures in Python
2.1 Arrays / Lists
(Python uses lists instead of arrays)
•	List operations (insert, delete, access)
•	Traversal
•	Slicing
•	2D lists (matrices)
Examples
•	Finding max/min
•	Reverse a list
•	Rotate array
•	Kadane’s algorithm
________________________________________
2.2 Strings
•	String manipulation
•	Palindrome checking
•	Anagrams
•	Pattern matching
•	Substrings & subsequences
________________________________________
2.3 Tuples
•	Immutable data handling
•	Tuple unpacking
•	Use cases in DSA
________________________________________
2.4 Sets
•	Union, intersection, difference
•	Removing duplicates
•	Hash based operations
________________________________________
2.5 Dictionaries (Hash Maps)
•	Key value storage
•	Frequency counting
•	Hashing concepts
•	Collision understanding (conceptual)
Common Problems
•	Two Sum
•	Frequency of elements
•	First non repeating character
________________________________________
3. Linear Data Structures
3.1 Stack
(LIFO – Last In First Out)
•	Implement using list
•	Push, pop, peek
•	Applications: 
o	Expression evaluation
o	Parenthesis checking
o	Undo/redo operations
________________________________________
3.2 Queue
(FIFO – First In First Out)
•	Using collections.deque
•	Circular queue
•	Priority queue (heap based)
________________________________________
3.3 Deque
•	Insert/delete from both ends
•	Sliding window problems
________________________________________
3.4 Linked List
(Not built in, implemented manually)
•	Singly linked list
•	Doubly linked list
•	Circular linked list
Operations
•	Insert, delete, search
•	Reverse a linked list
•	Detect loop (Floyd’s cycle detection)
________________________________________
4. Non Linear Data Structures
4.1 Trees
•	Tree terminology
•	Binary Tree
•	Binary Search Tree (BST)
•	Tree traversals: 
o	Inorder
o	Preorder
o	Postorder
o	Level order
Advanced Trees
•	AVL Tree
•	Heap (Min Heap & Max Heap)
________________________________________
4.2 Heap
•	Implement using heapq
•	Priority queues
•	Top K elements problems
________________________________________
4.3 Graphs
•	Graph representation: 
o	Adjacency list
o	Adjacency matrix
•	Directed vs Undirected
•	Weighted vs Unweighted
Graph Traversals
•	BFS (Breadth First Search)
•	DFS (Depth First Search)
Graph Algorithms
•	Shortest path (Dijkstra)
•	Cycle detection
•	Topological sorting
________________________________________
5. Algorithms
5.1 Searching Algorithms
•	Linear search
•	Binary search (iterative & recursive)
________________________________________
5.2 Sorting Algorithms
•	Bubble sort
•	Selection sort
•	Insertion sort
•	Merge sort
•	Quick sort
•	Heap sort
•	Counting sort
________________________________________
5.3 Recursion & Backtracking
•	Recursive functions
•	Stack behavior
•	Backtracking problems: 
o	N Queens
o	Sudoku solver
o	Permutations & combinations
________________________________________
5.4 Divide and Conquer
•	Merge sort
•	Quick sort
•	Binary search
________________________________________
5.5 Greedy Algorithms
•	Activity selection
•	Coin change (greedy version)
•	Minimum spanning tree concepts
________________________________________
5.6 Dynamic Programming (DP)
•	Memoization
•	Tabulation
•	Overlapping subproblems
•	Optimal substructure
Classic DP Problems
•	Fibonacci
•	Knapsack
•	Longest Common Subsequence (LCS)
•	Longest Increasing Subsequence (LIS)
________________________________________
6. Algorithmic Paradigms
•	Brute force
•	Two pointer technique
•	Sliding window
•	Hashing
•	Greedy
•	Backtracking
•	Dynamic programming
________________________________________
7. Time & Space Complexity
•	Big O, Big Ω, Big Θ
•	Best, average, worst case
•	Optimizing Python code for DSA
________________________________________
8. Python Specific DSA Tools
•	collections (deque, Counter, defaultdict)
•	heapq
•	bisect
•	itertools
•	functools.lru_cache (DP optimization)
________________________________________
9. Practice Platforms (Python Friendly)
•	LeetCode
•	GeeksforGeeks
•	HackerRank
•	CodeChef
•	Codeforces
________________________________________
10. Interview Focused DSA Topics (Very Important)
•	Arrays & Strings
•	HashMap problems
•	Stack & Queue
•	Trees and BST
•	Graph basics (BFS/DFS)
•	Recursion & DP
•	Sliding window & two pointers
________________________________________
✅ Suggested Learning Order
1.	Python basics
2.	Arrays & strings
3.	Stack, queue, linked list
4.	Searching & sorting
5.	Recursion & backtracking
6.	Trees & BST
7.	Heaps & graphs
8.	Dynamic programming
