Below is a clean, printable Dynamic Programming (DP) cheat sheet you can save as PDF or print directly.
It’s designed for quick revision during interviews and practice—minimal text, maximum clarity.
________________________________________
🧠 Dynamic Programming (DP) Cheat Sheet – Python
________________________________________
✅ What Is Dynamic Programming?
DP = Solving problems by breaking them into smaller overlapping subproblems and storing results.
DP Works When:
✔ Overlapping subproblems
✔ Optimal substructure
________________________________________
🧩 Two Ways to Do DP
1️⃣ Memoization (Top Down)
•	Recursive
•	Uses cache (dict / lru_cache)
•	Easy to write
from functools import lru_cache

@lru_cache(None)
def dp(i):
    if i <= base:
        return value
    return dp(i-1) + dp(i-2)
________________________________________
2️⃣ Tabulation (Bottom Up)
•	Iterative
•	Fast and interview preferred
dp = [0] * (n+1)
dp[0] = base

for i in range(1, n+1):
    dp[i] = dp[i-1] + dp[i-2]
________________________________________
🧠 DP Thinking Framework (IMPORTANT)
Before coding, answer:
1.	What does dp[i] mean?
2.	How to transition?
3.	What are base cases?
4.	Return final state
________________________________________
🔹 Core DP Patterns (Must Memorize)
________________________________________
✅ 1️⃣ 1D Linear DP
Pattern
dp[i] = best result till index i
✅ Problems:
•	Fibonacci
•	Climbing Stairs
•	House Robber
•	Maximum Subarray
dp[i] = max(dp[i-1], nums[i] + dp[i-2])
________________________________________
✅ 2️⃣ Take / Skip Pattern
Decision DP
✅ Problems:
•	House Robber
•	Subset problems
take = nums[i] + dp[i-2]
skip = dp[i-1]
dp[i] = max(take, skip)
________________________________________
✅ 3️⃣ 0/1 Knapsack (Subset DP)
Pattern
dp[i][w] = max value using first i items with capacity w
✅ Problems:
•	0/1 Knapsack
•	Partition Equal Subset
•	Target Sum
if wt[i-1] <= w:
    dp[i][w] = max(val[i-1] + dp[i-1][w-wt[i-1]], dp[i-1][w])
else:
    dp[i][w] = dp[i-1][w]
________________________________________
✅ 4️⃣ Unbounded Knapsack
(items can be reused)
✅ Problems:
•	Coin Change
•	Rod Cutting
dp[i][w] = max(val[i] + dp[i][w-wt[i]], dp[i-1][w])
________________________________________
✅ 5️⃣ String DP
Pattern
dp[i][j] = answer for first i chars and j chars
✅ Problems:
•	LCS
•	Edit Distance
•	Palindromic Subsequence
if s1[i-1] == s2[j-1]:
    dp[i][j] = 1 + dp[i-1][j-1]
else:
    dp[i][j] = max(dp[i-1][j], dp[i][j-1])
________________________________________
✅ 6️⃣ Grid DP
Movement DP
✅ Problems:
•	Unique Paths
•	Min Path Sum
dp[i][j] = dp[i-1][j] + dp[i][j-1]
________________________________________
⚡ Space Optimization Trick
If dp[i] depends only on previous values:
✅ Replace array with variables
prev2, prev1 = 0, 1
for _ in range(2, n+1):
    curr = prev1 + prev2
    prev2 = prev1
    prev1 = curr
Space: O(1) ✅
________________________________________
🚦 Common DP Base Cases
•	dp[0] = 0
•	dp[1] = value
•	Empty string → 0
•	Out of bounds → ignore
________________________________________
⛔ Common DP Mistakes
❌ Wrong dp definition
❌ Missing base cases
❌ Off by one errors
❌ No memoization → TLE
❌ Jumping to DP without recursion
________________________________________
🧪 Interview DP Strategy
1️⃣ Write brute force
2️⃣ Add memoization
3️⃣ Convert to tabulation
4️⃣ Optimize space (if asked)
________________________________________
🎯 DP Keywords → Use DP
•	Maximum / Minimum
•	Number of ways
•	Longest / Shortest
•	Optimal
•	Can you partition?
________________________________________
✅ DP Master Checklist
✔ Can define DP state quickly
✔ Recognize pattern in <30 seconds
✔ Convert recursion → DP
✔ Optimize space confidently
________________________________________
🖨️ Printing Tips
•	Copy → Paste into Word / Google Docs
•	Use A4, Portrait
•	Font: Consolas / Courier New
•	Print as 1–2 pages
________________________________________
If you want, I can: ✅ Convert this into a PDF file ✅ Make a one page ultra compact version ✅ Add LeetCode problem references per pattern ✅ Create a DP formula sheet
Just tell me 👍

